messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /printshops/{id}

- All HTTP methods acceptable:
  false

- HEAD:
  false

- POST:
  false

- OPTIONS:
  false

- TRACE:
  false

- GET:
  true

- PUT:
  false

- DELETE:
  false

- PATCH:
  false

Explanation:
- The controller class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so the method-level path "/printshops/{id}" is the full path.
- The getPrintShop(...) handler is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{id}", method = RequestMethod.GET), so it explicitly accepts only GET requests.
- Because the method attribute is explicitly RequestMethod.GET, other HTTP methods are not mapped in the code, so they are marked as not acceptable.
- Although some frameworks/servers may implicitly handle HEAD by delegating to GET at runtime, the determination above is made strictly from the source code annotations (per instructions), so HEAD is marked false.
